AST RESEARCH TECHNICAL BULLETIN TB-0159                  04-11-86


         TRANSMITTING A FILE WITH 0 BYTES USING AST-3780   


AST  recommends that users avoid transmitting files with 0 bytes.  
If the user attempts to transmit a file with 0 bytes, the speaker 
will  beep  twice and the following error message will appear  at 
the bottom of the screen.

***PARAMETER ERROR*** check emdat.prm***

r= 62 1=3200 b=8712 q= 0
